[I] A statically typed compiled systems programming language

[T] Nim is a statically typed compiled systems programming language. It
[T] combines successful concepts from mature languages like Python, Ada
[T] and Modula.

[U] https://nim-lang.org

[A] Andreas Rumpf
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

